      <me>
        A = \begin{bmatrix}
        2 \amp 4 \\ 4 \amp 2
        \end{bmatrix}
      </me>. <!-- 1, 3 -->
      Find the characteristic polynomial and the eigenvalues of <m>A</m>. 
    </p>
  </statement>
</exercise>
<exercise>
  <statement>
    <p>
      Let <m>A \in M_3(\rr)</m> be the following matrix: 
      <me>
        A = \begin{bmatrix}
        3 \amp 0 \amp 0 \\ 
        5 \amp -1 \amp 1 \\ 
        3 \amp -1 \amp 1
        \end{bmatrix}
      </me>. <!-- 0, 3 -->
      Find the characteristic polynomial and the eigenvalues of <m>A</m>. 
    </p>
  </statement>
</exercise>
